      <div class="container"> </br></br>
  
      <h2><u>How does your service stand out?</u></h2>

<p>In addition to teaching piano, I am also a music therapist and accept special needs students on piano as well as for therapeutic intervention. I have a Bachelor of Music from Temple University and a Master's in Creative Arts therapy from Hahnemann (Drexel University). I accept clients from birth to 100 for therapy and from age 5 to 100 for piano lessons featuring the Simply Music learning method.</p>

<h2><u>What do you enjoy about the work you do?</u></h1>

<p>I work with children as well as adults doing piano instruction as well as students of all ages with special needs doing piano instruction and/or music therapy.  I enjoy the diversity and challenge of working with various ages.</p>

<h2><u>What is your typical process for working with a new student?</u></h2>

<p>We would discuss the student's musical background and interests in order to develop a personalized lesson plan.  I will discuss with parents their roll in encouraging the music development of their child.</p>

<h2><u>What types of students have you worked with?</u></h2>

<p>I have worked with all ages and abilities from young children, teens and adults with special needs to children, teens and adults who don't have any disability.  Each student is unique and I taylor the lessons to needs and interests.</p>
